==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Impassible
<hw>Im*pas"si*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>impassibilis</ets>; pref. <ets>im-</ets> not +
<ets>passibilis</ets> passable: cf. F. <ets>impassible</ets>. See
<er>Passible</er>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of suffering; inaccessible to
harm or pain; not to be touched or moved to passion or sympathy;
unfeeling, or not showing feeling; without sensation.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Impassible</xex> to the critic.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir W.
Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Secure of death, I should contemn thy dart⟦br⟧
Though naked, and <qex>impassible</qex> depart.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Impassibleness</ent>⟦br⟧
